=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Vaping
Date: 7 February 2023
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Oral Answer)
Topic: Review of enforcement measures and effectiveness of vaping ban

Summary:

- Questions:
  1. Whether there will be a review of enforcement measures on vaping users and sellers of vaporisers and consumables.
  2. Whether the outright ban on vaporisers (since 1 Feb 2018) is effective, and reasons for the continued rise in vaping over the past three years.

- MOH Response:
  1. Harms of e-vaporisers are well established; MOH takes a multi-pronged approach to curb illicit sales and use.
  2. Health Sciences Authority (HSA):
     - Oversees enforcement of vaping regulations.
     - Works closely with Immigration & Checkpoints Authority (ICA) to curb illegal imports.
  3. Education & Awareness:
     - MOH and Health Promotion Board (HPB) collaborate with Ministry of Education (MOE) to raise awareness in schools.
     - Schools take serious disciplinary actions against vaping.
  4. Reasons for continued rise in vaping:
     - Attractive packaging, variety of flavours and scents.
     - Easy access through e-commerce platforms.
     - Misconceptions about the harms of e-vaporisers.
  5. MOH is closely monitoring vaping trends and reviewing the overall strategy.
     - Plans to strengthen enforcement and education measures in partnership with other agencies.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
- Immigration & Checkpoints Authority (ICA)
- Health Promotion Board (HPB)
- Ministry of Education (MOE)
- Schools

Key Concepts:
- Multi-pronged enforcement strategy
- Education and awareness in schools
- Review and strengthening of enforcement and education measures
- Factors contributing to rise in vaping: packaging, flavours, accessibility, misconceptions
